00:05:55.440 --> 00:06:01.080
[Amit Varma]: And I want to start off by sort of referring to an episode with you and indeed your book

00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:03.400
[Amit Varma]: on the BJP really eye-opening for me.

00:06:03.400 --> 00:06:08.200
[Amit Varma]: And I want to start off by asking you about something that we spoke about.

00:06:08.200 --> 00:06:11.560
[Amit Varma]: And then subsequently, you know, there's been a counter narrative to that.

00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:15.920
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, when Dhirendra Jha's book Gandhi's Assassins came out recently, there was a prominent blurb

00:06:15.920 --> 00:06:19.720
[Amit Varma]: by Christophe Jaffrelot saying that, oh, to the effect of, I don't remember the exact

00:06:19.720 --> 00:06:24.120
[Amit Varma]: words, but to the effect of this proves that the RSS was involved in Gandhi's murder.

00:06:24.120 --> 00:06:29.920
[Amit Varma]: And when we spoke, you pointed out how, yeah, Godse was in the RSS in the 1930s.

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:34.280
[Amit Varma]: But then by the early 1940s, he had, I mean, he didn't formally resign, but he had nothing

00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:35.280
[Amit Varma]: to do with them.

00:06:35.280 --> 00:06:41.800
[Amit Varma]: And most importantly, in his magazine Agrani, for years before he assassinated Gandhiji,

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:46.920
[Amit Varma]: he railed against two targets, which were RSS and Gandhiji, which kind of, you know,

00:06:46.920 --> 00:06:51.320
[Amit Varma]: proves that he would have had nothing to, you know, he was completely out of the RSS

00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:52.320
[Amit Varma]: orbit.

00:06:52.320 --> 00:06:57.480
[Amit Varma]: And this book using mostly circumstantial evidence claims seems to imply that, no, he

00:06:57.480 --> 00:07:02.560
[Amit Varma]: was an active part of the RSS, which I didn't see any direct evidence for it was circumstantial.

00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:06.240
[Amit Varma]: And also that the RSS is involved in the murder.

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:10.960
[Amit Varma]: So firstly, you know, what would your response to that be?

00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:17.520
[Amit Varma]: And secondly, the broader question is, is that, you know, I abhor the RSS and obviously

00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.160
[Amit Varma]: abhor Godse as well.

00:07:19.160 --> 00:07:24.200
[Amit Varma]: And I don't think that one needs to associate them necessarily and force fit them together

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:25.800
[Amit Varma]: to be against them.

00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:31.120
[Amit Varma]: So it's almost as if that this narrative is important for people to prove as they've been

00:07:31.120 --> 00:07:35.560
[Amit Varma]: kind of talking about for the last, you know, since Gandhiji died.

00:07:35.560 --> 00:07:37.920
[Guest]: So what's your take on this?

00:07:37.920 --> 00:07:43.480
[Guest]: Well, let's stick to the facts for a minute before, you know, the larger narrative, right?

00:07:43.480 --> 00:07:50.280
[Guest]: It's a clear fact that Godse was a Hindu nationalist in that he believed in Hindutva.

00:07:50.280 --> 00:07:52.520
[Guest]: He was a fan of Savarkar.

00:07:52.520 --> 00:07:58.600
[Guest]: The criticisms that he had of Gandhi are the exact criticisms the RSS had of Gandhi.

00:07:58.600 --> 00:07:59.960
[Guest]: There's no disagreement on that.

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:03.920
[Guest]: Even the RSS would say that, look, we may respect Gandhi, but these are the criticisms

00:08:03.920 --> 00:08:08.960
[Guest]: we had of him, etc, etc, appeasing Muslims, appeasing Muslim League, you know, appeasing

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:12.520
[Guest]: Pakistan after creation of Pakistan, etc, etc.

00:08:12.520 --> 00:08:18.400
[Guest]: So both Godse and the RSS had the same views on Gandhi.

00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:22.840
[Guest]: The question and the question for criminal liability is, was the RSS involved in the

00:08:22.840 --> 00:08:24.480
[Guest]: murder of Mahatma Gandhi?

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:27.240
[Guest]: There is no evidence for that, right?

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:32.120
[Guest]: There's a little more circumstantial evidence that says, look, what's the role of Savarkar,

00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:33.120
[Guest]: right?

00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:37.280
[Guest]: But in the, and this is not a question that has not been asked.

00:08:37.280 --> 00:08:41.680
[Guest]: This is a question that has been asked heavily for the last 75 years.

00:08:41.680 --> 00:08:45.640
[Guest]: Immediately after Gandhi's murder, RSS was banned.

00:08:45.640 --> 00:08:51.520
[Guest]: The police, which was run by Patel, was not sympathetic to the RSS at all.

00:08:51.520 --> 00:08:55.840
[Guest]: And a year later, they found no evidence against the RSS, which is why they removed the ban

00:08:55.840 --> 00:08:56.840
[Guest]: on the RSS.

00:08:56.840 --> 00:08:59.240
[Guest]: Why would they remove the ban if the RSS was involved, right?

00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:03.400
[Guest]: The RSS was not charge-sheeted, people were arrested, but nobody in the RSS was convicted

00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:05.280
[Guest]: or punished for this.

00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:09.640
[Guest]: And for decades later, this question has been asked again and again and again, right?

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:14.600
[Guest]: And as you point out, the new book is, you know, is circumstantial evidence and you have

00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:17.280
[Guest]: to then ask the question, why are we interested in that today?

00:09:17.280 --> 00:09:23.000
[Guest]: Because somehow you want to tarnish the BJP today with something that happened 75 years

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:27.400
[Guest]: ago and on which so much research has already been done, right?

00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:31.280
[Guest]: And as you said, why can't you just criticize the BJP saying that, you know, and I do that

00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:35.960
[Guest]: in my book saying that, you know, it's treatment of Muslims is unconscionable, etc, etc, etc.

00:09:35.960 --> 00:09:38.640
[Guest]: Why do you have to invent these other things, right?

00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:42.900
[Guest]: The other thing that has constantly been, I would say, invented on the BJP is that it's

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:46.680
[Guest]: fundamentally a Brahminical upper-caste organization.

00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:47.880
[Guest]: It's not.

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:53.200
[Guest]: And if it has that in the beginning, it's certainly not the case under Modi and, you

00:09:53.200 --> 00:09:58.080
[Guest]: know, Amit, I keep wondering, why can't you just say the problem with the BJP is that

00:09:58.080 --> 00:10:04.920
[Guest]: it's majoritarian, that, you know, 200 million Indian citizens it seeks to exclude from citizenship.

00:10:04.920 --> 00:10:06.300
[Guest]: That's bad enough, right?

00:10:06.300 --> 00:10:10.600
[Guest]: Why do you have to, you know, and the problem with doing this and especially things like

00:10:10.600 --> 00:10:14.840
[Guest]: the relationship between RSS and Gandhi's murder, which, by the way, was a Congress

00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:20.120
[Guest]: political platform for decades after, which is, you know, vote mat de do Gandhi ke hatyaron

00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:21.120
[Guest]: ko.

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:24.780
[Guest]: That used to be the voting rallying cry, but there's just no evidence for that.

00:10:24.780 --> 00:10:30.360
[Guest]: And I feel in some senses, you know, critics of the BJP do themselves disservice with these

00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:36.320
[Guest]: kind of allegations that have been exhaustively studied and exhaustively disproved over seven

00:10:36.320 --> 00:10:37.320
[Guest]: decades.

00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:38.320
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, absolutely.

00:10:38.320 --> 00:10:41.160
[Amit Varma]: And, and Dhilendra Jha, by the way, is a wonderful writer.

00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:42.160
[Amit Varma]: So it's not about him as well.

00:10:42.160 --> 00:10:46.880
[Amit Varma]: I loved his previous two books, which I recommend you read, called The Dark Knight and Ascetic

00:10:46.880 --> 00:10:47.880
[Amit Varma]: Games.

00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:51.040
[Amit Varma]: The Dark Knight, in fact, has a history of how the whole Babri Masjid controversy started.

00:10:51.040 --> 00:10:53.680
[Amit Varma]: Akar Patel first told me about that book.

00:10:53.680 --> 00:10:56.020
[Amit Varma]: So a wonderful journalist, not a knock on him.

00:10:56.020 --> 00:11:01.120
[Amit Varma]: And this book also has some excellent journalism slash history and, you know, all of that.

00:11:01.120 --> 00:11:07.520
[Amit Varma]: But it also seems that there is, you know, a need to kind of push a narrative about a

00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:09.800
[Amit Varma]: party where absolutely everything is black.

00:11:09.800 --> 00:11:13.560
[Amit Varma]: And if this has become a dominant narrative that the RSS killed Gandhi, then they've got

00:11:13.560 --> 00:11:17.900
[Amit Varma]: to find a way to kind of talk about it, where I found, you know, my conversation with you

00:11:17.900 --> 00:11:22.120
[Amit Varma]: enlightening on this that, you know, Godse railed against them for years in his magazine

00:11:22.120 --> 00:11:23.120
[Amit Varma]: Agrani.

00:11:23.120 --> 00:11:27.280
[Amit Varma]: And yes, you can't necessarily absolve Savarkar in the same way.

00:11:27.280 --> 00:11:30.080
[Amit Varma]: But that's again, a whole different story.

00:11:30.080 --> 00:11:35.360
[Amit Varma]: And as far as caste is concerned, you know, the fact is that both in 2014 and 2019, more

00:11:35.360 --> 00:11:38.320
[Amit Varma]: Dalits voted for the BJP than they did for any other party.

00:11:38.320 --> 00:11:40.680
[Guest]: And it's the same with OBCs and tribals too.

00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:41.680
[Amit Varma]: Exactly.

00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:46.520
[Amit Varma]: Casteism is pernicious and is unfortunately still a part of Hindu society.

00:11:46.520 --> 00:11:48.560
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, and that's a terrible thing.

00:11:48.560 --> 00:11:52.260
[Amit Varma]: And hopefully one day we get past it, though we are nowhere close to doing so.

00:11:52.260 --> 00:11:56.180
[Amit Varma]: But that doesn't mean that Hindutva per se is necessarily casteist.

00:11:56.180 --> 00:12:02.640
[Amit Varma]: What Hindutva is, especially as we see it today, is anti Muslim and, you know, and that

00:12:02.640 --> 00:12:03.640
[Amit Varma]: is a big problem.

00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:09.040
[Amit Varma]: And that's reason enough, I think, in my mind to sort of oppose it.

00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:12.720
[Amit Varma]: You know, you've mentioned to me that you've never voted for the BJP and why and so on

00:12:12.720 --> 00:12:13.720
[Amit Varma]: and so forth.

00:12:13.720 --> 00:12:18.760
[Amit Varma]: And we've just kind of spoken about the anti Muslimness and all of that.

00:12:18.760 --> 00:12:24.800
[Amit Varma]: But is it the case that after you came out with these two books on Narasimha Rao, which

00:12:24.800 --> 00:12:28.520
[Amit Varma]: we'll discuss in some detail and which I really love reading, and your book on the BJP for

00:12:28.520 --> 00:12:33.600
[Amit Varma]: Modi that people, especially within academia, within the world of history, began to look

00:12:33.600 --> 00:12:38.960
[Amit Varma]: at you differently, as if in some way, you are an apologist of some sort, just because

00:12:38.960 --> 00:12:40.160
[Amit Varma]: of the subject that you chose.

